<span id="xxi.ii.iv.vi-p44"></span> This expression, which repeatedly
occurs in this and the following sections, surely implies that there was
something economical in our Lord’s profession of ignorance. He said with
a purpose, not as a mere plain fact or doctrine. \[But see Prolegg. ch.
iv. §5.\]

